HEADWORD: Orientalism
<hw>O`ri*en"tal*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>orientalisme</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Any system, doctrine, custom, expression, etc.,
peculiar to Oriental people.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Knowledge or use of Oriental languages, history,
literature, etc.</def> <rj><au>London Quart. Rev.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orientalist</ent>⟦br⟧
